raw_data.title: Administrative Assistant
raw_data.description: Administrative Assistant, Performs clerical duties supporting office operations (e.g. preparing, receiving, reviewing and verifying documents).  Maintain office records. Compile data or information from various areas to produce reports.  Maintain maintenance and service records. Receives service requests and dispatches personnel.  Maintains HR files. Assist corporate ofc with processing payroll.

raw_data.title: Carpenter
raw_data.description: Performs carpentry duties to maintain in good condition building woodwork and accessories made of wood (e.g. counters, benches, partitions, doors, floors, stairs, casings, and trim. Work includes: Planning and preparing work through use of blueprints, drawings, models, or verbal instructions. May require the use of a variety of power and hand tools and standard measuring instruments. Able to make standard shop computations relating to dimensions of work.  Able to select materials necessary for individual jobs. Work of a maintenance carpenter requires rounded training and experience.

raw_data.title: Chief Building Engineer
raw_data.description: Operate facilities including physical structures, utilities and surrounding grounds. Operation includes programs and services essential to maintain a safe, healthy and comfortable environment. Maintain, repair/modify facilities by upgrading/replacing; inspecting; planning, overseeing and inspecting work performed by trades, laborers, subcontractors, and others; apply full range of principles, concepts and methods of facility operations to evaluate use patterns and maintenance/restoration requirements; apply manufacturer’s equipment maintenance and repair requirements; ensure quality and timeliness of work performed; ensure contract compliance; perform diagnostic inspections of structure, electrical/mechanical systems and equipment; prepare project scopes, descriptions and justifications; establish scheduling for all facility maintenance staff; provide HR function, as necessary; knowledgeable of OSHA, labor, federal, state and local regulations; ensure compliance with all certification, safety, fire prevention and security requirements; able to operate BAS; determining and projecting funding requirements.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Specialized Education and Additional Current Experience
raw_data.key_words: Operate facility,BAS,Maintenance and testing,Building Programs,Manage Personnel

labor_categories.years_experience: Specialized Education and Additional Current Experience

raw_data.title: Electrician
raw_data.description: Performs a variety of electrical trade functions (eg installation, maintenance, repair of equipment, distribution, or utilization of electric energy). Work includes: Installing or repairing a variety of electrical equipment (e.g. generators, transformers, switchboards, controllers, circuit breakers, motors, heating units, conduit systems, or other transmission equipment); working from blueprints, drawings, layouts, or other specifications; locating and diagnosing trouble in electrical system or equipment; working standard computations relating to load requirements of wiring or electrical equipment; and using a variety of electrician’s hand tools, measuring and testing instruments.

raw_data.title: Electronics Technician, Maintenance III
raw_data.description: Applies advanced technical knowledge to solve unusually complex problems that typically cannot be solved solely by referencing manufacturers’ manuals or similar documents. Examples of such problems include determining the location and density of circuitry, evaluating electromagnetic radiation, isolating malfunctions, and incorporating engineering changes. Work typically requires a detailed understanding of the interrelationships of circuits. Exercises independent judgment in performing such tasks as making circuit analyses, calculating wave forms, and tracing relationships in signal flow. Uses complex test instruments such as high frequency pulse generators, frequency synthesizers, distortion analyzers, and complex computer control equipment. Work may be reviewed by supervisor for general compliance with accepted practices. May provide technical guidance to lower level technicians.

raw_data.title: Fire Alarm Technician
raw_data.description: Performs repair, maintenance, installation, inspection and testing of fire alarm systems and components. Ability to detect, diagnose malfunctions, repair/replace parts or components, and align and calibrate. Responsible for the development and propagation of signals, measurement of forces, computation of data and control systems, as well as mechanical and hydraulic knowledge. Inspection in accordance with regulatory procedures and documents accordingly. Maintenance and repairs executed as per the manufacturer.
raw_data.required_certifications_or_licenses: Factory Cert, Certified by FA Organization, State License

raw_data.title: Gardener
raw_data.description: Maintains commercial or public property grounds. Includes lawns, campground, picnic area, park, playground, and athletic fields. Repairs equipment used for the task/job. Performs grass cutting with walking-type or riding mowers (less than 2000 lbs); trims hedges; edges around walks, flower beds and wells; prunes shrubs; sprays lawns, shrubs and trees with fertilizer or insecticide; plants grass, flowers, trees, and shrubs; waters lawns and shrubs during dry periods; picks up and removes leaves, paper or other litter.

raw_data.title: General Maintenance Worker
raw_data.description: Installs, services and repairs mechanical systems in office buildings and other commercial establishments, utilizing knowledge of operation, pipefitting, electrical and structural layout. Uses hand tools, follows blueprints or engineering specifications. Fabricates, assembles and installs ductwork and chassis parts. Cuts and bends tubing to correct length and shape. Cuts and threads pipe. Connects motors, compressors, etc. to control panels and connects control panels to power source. Observes gauges and adjusts controls to insure proper operation. Wraps pipes in insulation batting and secures them in place. Replaces defective breaker controls, thermostats, switches, fuses and electrical wiring to repair installed units. Uses a variety of hand and power tools, testing equipment, and gauges.

labor_categories.labor_category: Heating, Refrigeration and Air Condition Mechanic

raw_data.title: Heating, Refrigeration and Air Condition Mechanic
raw_data.description: Installs, services and repairs environmental-control systems in commercial buildings. Utilizes knowledge of refrigeration theory, pipefitting & structural layout. Mounts compressor and condenser units on platform or floor, following blueprints or engineering specifications. Fabricates, assembles and installs ductwork and chassis parts. Installs evaporator unit in chassis or in air-duct system. Cuts & bends tubing to correct length and shape. Cuts and threads pipe. Joins tubing or pipes to various refrigerating units. Installs expansion and discharge valves in circuit. Connects motors, compressors, temperature/humidity controls, and circulating ventilation fans to control panels and power source. Installs air and water filters in completed installation. Adds Freon gas to build up prescribed operating pressure. Adjusts controls to insure proper operation. Tests joints and connections for gas leaks. Replaces defective breaker controls, thermostats, switches, fuses and electrical wiring to repair installed units. May install, repair and service air conditioners, ranging from fifteen to twenty tons cooling capacity.
raw_data.required_certifications_or_licenses: Technical School Certification, Union Certification, State License

raw_data.title: Instrument Mechanic
raw_data.description: Installs, repairs, maintains and adjusts indicating, recording, telemetering, and controlling instruments used to measure and control variables, such as pressure, flow, temperature, motion, force, and chemical composition. Disassembles malfunctioning instruments and examines, tests mechanism and circuitry for defects. Troubleshoots equipment in or out of control system; replaces or repairs defective parts. Reassembles instrument and tests for conformance with specifications. Inspects instruments periodically and makes minor calibration adjustments to insure functioning within specified standards. May adjust and repair final control mechanisms. Calibrate instruments according to established standards.

raw_data.title: Janitor
raw_data.description: Cleans and keeps in an orderly condition shop working areas, washrooms, premises of an office, apartment house, commercial or other establishment. Duties involve a combination of: Sweeping, mopping, scrubbing and polishing floors; removing debris, trash, and other refuse; dusting equipment, furniture, or fixtures; polishing metal fixtures or trimmings; providing supplies and minor maintenance services; and cleaning lavatories, showers, and restrooms; cleaning/disinfecting daycare facility/space; clean/disinfact kitchenettes, workout rooms, and holding cells. Types of spaces include general office, laboratory/research, judicial, common, kitchenettes, auditorium, library, and historic spaces. Workers required to disassemble and assemble equipment in order to clean machinery.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Trade School, Professional Trade Organization Training

labor_categories.years_experience: Trade School, Professional Trade Organization Training

raw_data.title: Laborer
raw_data.description: Repair and maintain machines, mechanical equipment and buildings, with general skills in plumbing, electrical, air-conditioning and heating. Perform maintenance which includes painting, repairs on plaster, drywall, roofs, windows, doors, floors, woodwork and other parts of the building structures. Inspect and diagnose problems for corrective process utilizing blueprints, repair manuals and catalogs. Perform routine preventive maintenance inspecting drives, motors, belts, checking fluid levels, replace filters and other general maintenance, maintaining records of findings and actions.

raw_data.title: Landscaper
raw_data.description: Plans and executes small scale landscaping operations. Maintains grounds and landscape of household, business and other properties. Works with others in preparing and grading terrain, applying fertilizers, seeding/sodding lawns, and transplanting shrubs and plants. Plants new and repairs established lawns, using seed mixtures and fertilizers recommended for particular soil type and area location. Locates and plants shrubs, trees, and flowers for particular landscape effect or those selected by property owner. Mows and trims lawns using push/power machine. Trims shrubs and cultivates gardens. Sprays trees and shrubs and applies supplemental liquid and dry nutrients to lawn, trees and shrubs. Cleans ground, using rakes, brooms, and hose. May dig trenches and install drain tiles.

raw_data.title: Locksmith
raw_data.description: Install, repair, modify, and opens a variety of locking mechanisms found on doors, desks, compartments, mobile equipment, safes, and vaults. Examines locking mechanism and installs new unit; disassembles unit and replaces worn tumblers, springs, and other parts; or repairs them by filing, drilling, chiseling and grinding. Opens door locks by moving lockpick in cylinder or opens safe locks by listening to lock sounds or by drilling. Makes new or duplicate keys, using key cutting machine. Changes combination by inserting new or repaired tumblers into lock. Establishes keying systems for buildings.

raw_data.title: Machinery Maintenance Mechanic
raw_data.description: Repairs machinery or mechanical equipment. Work involves: examining machines and mechanical equipment to diagnose source of trouble; partial or total dismantling of machines and performing repairs; replacing broken or defective parts; ordering the production of a replacement part by a machine shop or sending the machine to a machine shop for major repairs; preparing written specifications for major repairs or for the production of parts ordered; reassembling machines making necessary adjustments for operation. In general, the work of a Machinery Maintenance Mechanic requires rounded training and experience usually acquired through F11a formal apprenticeship or equivalent training and experience.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Trade School, F11a formal apprenticeship or equivalent training and experience

labor_categories.years_experience: Trade School, F11a formal apprenticeship or equivalent training and experience

raw_data.title: Painter, Maintenance
raw_data.description: Paints and redecorates walls, woodwork and fixtures. Work involves: knowledge of surface peculiarities and types of paint required for different applications; preparing surface for painting by removing old finish or placing putty/filler in nail holes and interstices; and applying paint with spray gun or brush. May mix colors, oils, white lead and other paint ingredients to obtain proper color or consistency.

raw_data.title: Pest Controller
raw_data.description: Sprays chemical solutions or toxic gases; sets mechanical traps to kill pests that infest buildings and surrounding areas. Fumigates rooms and buildings, using toxic gases. Sprays chemical solutions or dusts powders in rooms and work areas. Places poisonous paste, bait and/or mechanical traps where pests are present. May clean areas that harbor pests, using rakes, brooms, shovels, and mops preparatory to fumigating.

raw_data.title: Pipefitter Maintenance, Plumber Maintenance
raw_data.description: Pipefitter: Installs/repairs water, steam, gas or other types of pipe & fittings. Work involves: Laying out work, locate position of pipe using drawings/written specifications; cutting various sizes of pipe lengths; threading pipes; bending pipe; assembling pipe and fastening to hangers; make computations relating to pressures, flow and size of pipe required; and make standard tests to ensure finished pipes meet specifications.  Plumber: Assembles, installs and repairs pipes; fittings and fixtures of heating, water, and drainage systems, according to specifications and plumbing codes. Based on plans and drawings determines personnel and sequence of installations. Inspects structure to ascertain obstructions to be avoided. Locates and marks position of pipe and connections; cuts passage holes for pipes in walls and floors. Cuts and threads pipe. Bends pipe to required angle. Assembles and installs valves, pipe fittings, and pipes composed of metals and nonmetals. Joins pipes. Fills pipe system with water or air and reads pressure gauges to determine whether system is leaking. Installs and repairs plumbing fixtures. Repairs and maintains plumbing (eg replacing washers, mending burst pipes, and opening clogged drains)

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: Plan, design and manage building/ facilities/campuses, grounds, equipment, supplies and personnel necessary for the efficient operation of the facility. This includes proper scheduling of all maintenance, repairs and/or replacement of mechanical equipment; scheduling of janitorial and grounds maintenance functions. Oversee renovation projects as applicable.  Provide HR function, to include appropriate and required training. Conduct scheduled and unscheduled inspection of services to ensure contractual obligations are being met and/or exceeded.  The Project Manager is essentially the guardian of the facility ensuring all components are functioning properly, from interior, exterior, and human.

raw_data.title: Snow Remover
raw_data.description: Laborer, Grounds Maintenance - Snow Remover: Maintains walks and lots of industrial, commercial or public property.  Removes snow and ice from walks, driveways, roads, or parking lots, using shovel, snow thrower, or truck with blade.  Spreads salt on walkways and other areas. Vigilent in weather watching to predict crew needs (i.e. accumulation throughout day, when storm predicted to start and end). Schedules accordingly and orders sufficient supplies for season.

raw_data.title: Tree Trimmer
raw_data.description: Prunes trees to shape and improve growth; prevent interference with power lines and structures; or potential over growth that poses a safety hazard. Sprays trees and applies supplemental liquid and dry nutrients to trees. Recommends removal/replacement for dying or diseased trees.
